Its tiny heel and ankle stout,
His Arms were two twin Oaks, his Legs so stout
line_2: That they might bear a Mansion House about,

line_1: Not, as old Fame reports, wise, generous, bold, and stout.

line_1: But plenty of good beer, both small and stout,
line_2: With wine of elder to prevent the gout.
I grieve your Brother has the Gout;
